		BLOCKER 3: Drone waypoints not advancing — counter logic bug
		════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

		WHAT WAS TRIED:
		  Waypoint navigator launched. Drone armed and hovered. Terminal immediately
		  printed "All waypoints complete — holding position" without moving.

		SYMPTOMS:
		  - Drone at x≈0, y≈0, z≈-3m (just hovering home)
		  - waypoint_navigator logged "All waypoints complete" on first check
		  - Drone never moved toward any waypoint

		DIAGNOSIS STEPS:
		  1. Added logging to print distance to each waypoint at each tick
		  2. Discovered: drone starts at x=0.05, y=-0.02 which is within ARRIVE_DIST
		     (0.5m) of WP0=[0,0,-3] immediately
		  3. WP0 marked done → check WP1, also within distance → check WP2...
		     All waypoints passed in first tick because drone starts near WP0

		ROOT CAUSE:
		  Waypoint logic checked distance on first tick before drone was stable.
		  Distance threshold too loose. Waypoints too close to starting position.

		FIX (iterative):
		  First fix: increased ARRIVE_DIST, added hold time → still buggy
		  Second fix: rewrote as time-based (hold each waypoint N seconds regardless
		  of position) → simpler, worked reliably
		  Final fix: removed waypoints entirely, switched to single target point with
		  timer-based advance (fly to x=20 after 8 seconds, detect along the way)

