		BLOCKER 5: NED vs ENU axis confusion — drone flying wrong direction
		════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

		WHAT WAS SEEN:
		  Boxes placed at Gazebo x=4, y=0. Drone target set to NED x=4, y=0.
		  Drone and boxes were visually going in perpendicular directions in Gazebo.

		DIAGNOSIS:
		  Gazebo uses ENU (East-North-Up):
		    Gazebo X = East
		    Gazebo Y = North

		  PX4 NED (North-East-Down):
		    NED X = North
		    NED Y = East

		  Conversion:
		    Gazebo X → NED Y (East)
		    Gazebo Y → NED X (North)

		  Boxes at Gazebo (4, 0) = NED (0, 4) — East
		  Drone target NED (4, 0) — North
		  Completely perpendicular. Drone flies North, boxes are East.

		FIX:
		  Updated world file box positions to Gazebo ENU coordinates that map to
		  the drone's NED flight path.

		  Drone flies NED x=+positive (North)
		  In Gazebo ENU that is Y axis positive
		  So box goes at Gazebo (0, 8) = NED (8, 0) ✓

		  This took multiple iterations to get right. Intermediate incorrect attempt
		  placed boxes at Gazebo (0, -4), (0, -8), (0, -12) mapping to NED (-4, 0)
		  which is South — drone was flying North. Still wrong.

		  Final correct setup:
		    World file: <pose>0 8 0 0 0 0</pose>  ← Gazebo ENU (0, 8) = NED (8, 0)
		    Navigator: self._send_position(20.0, 0.0, -3.0)  ← NED North, passes x=8

