		BLOCKER 6: Drone landing outside the box
		════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

		WHAT WAS SEEN:
		  DETECTED triggered but drone landed 1-2m away from red box.
		  Multiple attempts with different threshold values still missed.

		ROOT CAUSE (diagnosed iteratively):

		  Attempt 1: Threshold too low (area < 500)
		    Detection fired when drone first glimpsed red from far away at an angle.
		    Saved position was drone location when red was at edge of frame — offset
		    from actual box center.

		  Attempt 2: Increased threshold to 3000, then 8000
		    Helped but not enough. Drone still moving fast when detection triggered.

		  Attempt 3: Single detection save
		    First detection was always at an angle, coordinates always offset.

		FINAL FIX:
		  Wait for 5 detections before confirming position. Update saved coordinates
		  on every detection. By detection 5 the drone has more frame coverage and
		  the saved position is the most centered average.

		  self._detect_count += 1
		  self._box_x = self._cur_x  ← update every time, not just first
		  self._box_y = self._cur_y
		  if self._detect_count >= 5:
		      self._box_found = True

		  Combined with: return above saved position at altitude BEFORE descending,
		  not descend from wherever detection happened.

