		BLOCKER 7: Drone bouncing on landing
		════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

		WHAT WAS SEEN:
		  Used VEHICLE_CMD_NAV_LAND command. Drone descended then bounced violently
		  on touchdown — went back up 2-3m then crashed.

		ROOT CAUSE:
		  PX4 SITL's landing controller uses aggressive touchdown detection.
		  In Gazebo Classic with default physics, the impact detection triggers
		  a rapid disarm which causes the drone to fall, hit the ground, and
		  bounce due to collision physics.

		FIX:
		  Replaced VEHICLE_CMD_NAV_LAND with manual position control descent.
		  Incrementally raise z setpoint from -3.0 to 0.0 at 0.02m per tick:

		  self._land_z += 0.02   # 10Hz × 0.02 = 0.2 m/s descent rate
		  self._send_position(self._box_x, self._box_y, self._land_z)

		  Smooth descent, no bounce, no handoff to PX4 landing controller.

		--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
		SECTION 6 — WHAT WOULD BE IMPROVED WITH MORE TIME
		--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

		1. REPLACE HSV WITH ARUCO MARKER DETECTION
		   HSV is fragile — Gazebo lighting, pad color rendering, and camera exposure
		   all affect it. ArUco markers provide sub-centimeter pose estimation from a
		   single camera frame. The drone would know not just "red is there" but exact
		   3D position and orientation of the marker.
		   Implementation: cv2.aruco.detectMarkers() — already in OpenCV.
		   PX4 has built-in precision landing support for this via IRLock.

		2. CLOSED-LOOP LANDING USING PIXEL OFFSET
		   Currently the drone saves a NED position when detection confirms and flies
		   back to it. Better: once above the pad, use the pixel offset of the detected
		   centroid from image center to generate velocity corrections — fly toward
		   the center of the pad in real time. Higher precision, no coordinate frame
		   conversion needed.

		3. UPGRADE TO GAZEBO GARDEN + x500
		   x500 with Gazebo Garden has better camera, more realistic physics, and
		   native ROS 2 bridge without manual setup_gazebo.bash sourcing.
		   Blocked currently because the system has Gazebo Classic 11 only.


